Tropical storm Floyd was forecasted to become a hurricane, potentially threatening the Bahamas and the U.S. southeast.
Residents in Anguilla prepared for the storm by closing schools and putting up shutters.
Meteorologists predicted the hurricane to intensify and possibly hit the Abacos Islands and Eleuthera.
NASA planned to close the Kennedy Space Center as a precaution.
FEMA positioned supplies in Atlanta for quick deployment.
Evacuations were ordered in vulnerable coastal areas.
Officials urged individuals to prepare for the storm's impact.
Forecasters warned of potential catastrophic destruction.
Floyd's path remained uncertain, causing concern among residents and officials alike.
